The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning in cache management, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on computer systems and performance optimization, which suggests a potential fit for distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of advanced reinforcement learning architectures and multi-agent systems suggests a potential fit for machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses a database benchmark system to evaluate the proposed approach, which suggests a potential fit for databases (cs.DB).
